**近现代时期（19-20世纪）**
随着印度民族主义的兴起，耆那教学者开始重新审视印度教的圣地体系，试图在喜马拉雅山脉中寻找耆那教的独立圣地传统。冈仁波齐作为「八足山」的解读在这一时期得到更多关注。

**当代朝圣（21世纪）**
现代交通的发展使得越来越多的耆那教徒能够完成这一神圣的朝圣之旅。虽然人数相对较少，但耆那教徒对冈仁波齐的虔诚与其他宗教信徒并无二致。`,
    historyEn: `**Early History (6th Century BCE)**
Jainism was systematized by Mahavira (599-527 BCE), but tradition holds the first Tirthankara Rishabhanatha lived in much earlier times. Jain scriptures describe "Astapada" in abstract terms without clearly identifying today's specific peak in Tibet's Ngari Prefecture.

**Medieval Period (5th-15th Century)**
Jainism developed in western India (Gujarat, Rajasthan), forming distinctive temple architecture and iconographic traditions. But specific pilgrimage records to Kailash from this period are sparse. Jainism's Kailash connection appears more in canonical texts and cosmology than actual pilgrimage activity.

**Modern Period (19th-20th Century)**
With the rise of Indian nationalism, Jain scholars began re-examining Hindu sacred geography, seeking independent Jain sacred mountain traditions in the Himalayas. Kailash's interpretation as "Astapada" gained more attention during this period.

**Contemporary Pilgrimage (21st Century)**
Modern transportation has enabled increasing numbers of Jains to complete this sacred pilgrimage. Though relatively few in number, Jain devotion to Kailash is no less sincere than other religious believers.`
